Dialogue: 5,0:01:03.42,0:01:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no good!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:04.67,0:01:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The fire has spread to the forest in District Three!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:07.96,0:01:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't we get more fire choppers?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:10.47,0:01:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, the entire mountain will be destroyed!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:13.39,0:01:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it. Why is it spreading so fast?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:29.36,0:01:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What happened here?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:38.70,0:01:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The trees are all uprooted.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:40.91,0:01:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Did something crash-land here?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:43.29,0:01:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we haven't had any reports like that.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:50.05,0:01:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Mont Blanc... Mont Blanc...
Dialogue: 5,0:01:51.67,0:01:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Professor Reinhardt!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:53.43,0:01:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My Mont Blanc!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:56.39,0:01:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:58.10,0:01:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:59.14,0:02:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Professor! It's too dangerous!
Dialogue: 5,0:02:02.19,0:02:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,His signal is dead...
Dialogue: 5,0:02:04.02,0:02:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I've lost contact with Mont Blanc!
Dialogue: 5,0:03:11.46,0:03:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Gesicht?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:17.14,0:03:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:20.35,0:03:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem tired lately.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:22.56,0:03:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you overworking yourself?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:24.39,0:03:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you should take some time off...
Dialogue: 5,0:03:26.52,0:03:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:27.90,0:03:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to worry.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:34.65,0:03:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, white smoke is still rising after two days,
Dialogue: 5,0:03:39.03,0:03:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and scattered fires are visible.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:42.45,0:03:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,According to investigators on the scene,
Dialogue: 5,0:03:44.62,0:03:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the robot assigned to \Nthe Swiss Forestry Service, Mont Blanc,
Dialogue: 5,0:03:48.83,0:03:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,was found in pieces at the site of the forest fire.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:53.84,0:03:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Mont Blanc was a world-renowned mountain guide
Dialogue: 5,0:03:58.51,0:04:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,known for befriending scores of \Nchildren and mountain climbers alike.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:02.22,0:04:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He also poured himself into programming a tree-clearing \Nstrategy that allows us to coexist with nature.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:08.64,0:04:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Condolences for the beloved Mont Blanc \Nare coming in from all over the world.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:20.11,0:04:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is Gesicht.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:23.87,0:04:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:26.08,0:04:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:28.33,0:04:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's work.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:29.46,0:04:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to go.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:30.37,0:04:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? But what about your breakfast?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:43.47,0:04:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Helena.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:45.14,0:04:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we take a trip when I can take time off?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:49.60,0:04:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I should be getting more rest, right?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:52.86,0:04:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I never expected to hear you say that.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:16.13,0:05:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The victim resided in this apartment. \NBernard Lanke, 42 years old.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:20.13,0:05:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a leader of a group \Nthat defends the Robot Rights Laws.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:25.35,0:05:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Was he human?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:27.06,0:05:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he was.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:31.89,0:05:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, this is awful.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:41.40,0:05:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You there!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:43.99,0:05:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd appreciate if you didn't just \Nwalk all over my crime scene.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:46.83,0:05:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector, he's the one sent from Europol.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:55.42,0:05:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:56.29,0:05:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Pardon me.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:58.63,0:06:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Inspector Wallace with the city police.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:00.84,0:06:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:02.05,0:06:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, the place has been turned upside down.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:05.22,0:06:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll take us a while to figure out if anything has been taken.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:10.31,0:06:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I don't believe this is the work of a thief.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:13.89,0:06:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? How can you be sure?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:16.11,0:06:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no sign anything is missing.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:17.82,0:06:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. The room's been trashed. How can you tell?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:20.78,0:06:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:21.99,0:06:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This room was merely damaged.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:26.49,0:06:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what do you make of this?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:41.92,0:06:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are things shoved into the\N victim's head to look like horns?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:49.47,0:06:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's me.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:51.60,0:06:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:52.43,0:06:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:55.85,0:06:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone broke through a checkpoint!
Dialogue: 5,0:07:12.91,0:07:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Get an ambulance right away!
Dialogue: 5,0:07:18.63,0:07:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you the only one attacked, patrolman?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:21.63,0:07:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Robby was also at the checkpoint...
Dialogue: 5,0:07:27.09,0:07:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My partner...
Dialogue: 5,0:07:28.93,0:07:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, a patrol-bot...
Dialogue: 5,0:07:31.76,0:07:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Model PRC-1332.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:42.19,0:07:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe a patrol-bot was destroyed so easily.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:48.78,0:07:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 5,0:07:50.70,0:07:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,A male suspect in his twenties in \Na red cap with tattoos on both arms
Dialogue: 5,0:07:55.20,0:07:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,seems to have fled toward \Nthe old city's redevelopment zone.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:58.75,0:08:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it. Pair up and search—
Dialogue: 5,0:08:02.55,0:08:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! I said to pair up!
Dialogue: 5,0:08:07.68,0:08:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it! Europol, my ass!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:23.63,0:09:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop resisting!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:25.34,0:09:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't do anything!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:26.92,0:09:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There are traces of paint from \Nthe patrol-bot on that steel pipe.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:33.22,0:09:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A drug addict, huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:35.35,0:09:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You're high on a drug called "noi."
Dialogue: 5,0:09:37.10,0:09:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ingested about 40 minutes ago.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:39.10,0:09:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that about right?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:42.19,0:09:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's your dealer?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:45.56,0:09:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A guy named Shultz on Karl-Heinz Street.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:49.44,0:09:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What time did you meet him?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:52.07,0:09:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Around five this morning.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:54.57,0:09:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If the dealer corroborates your account, you have an alibi.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:00.45,0:10:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's around the time when Bernard Lanke was murdered.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:03.71,0:10:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Murdered?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:05.92,0:10:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You only attacked the patrolman \Nwith a pipe to avoid arrest for illicit drugs.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:12.01,0:10:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And you destroyed a patrol-bot, aka Robby.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:16.05,0:10:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I can read you your rights and arrest you quietly...
Dialogue: 5,0:10:31.40,0:10:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't shoot me!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:32.86,0:10:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Relax.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:34.32,0:10:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This gun only shoots sleeping gas.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:37.45,0:10:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm made in such a way that I can't hurt humans.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:40.49,0:10:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a robot.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:52.01,0:10:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes? Who is it?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:53.84,0:10:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Gesicht. I'm a special investigator from Europol.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:00.31,0:11:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I help you?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:01.56,0:11:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Robby's wife?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:03.81,0:11:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:05.98,0:11:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid I have bad news.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:15.86,0:11:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like some tea?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:18.24,0:11:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Being a robot as well, I'm sure you'll just \Ngo through the motions of drinking.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:23.79,0:11:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,By living as humans do, they say we robots \Ncan upgrade our human-like senses.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:31.42,0:11:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose that's true.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:34.42,0:11:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's difficult to understand the joy of drinking tea.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:38.55,0:11:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially for an outdated model like me.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:44.89,0:11:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I work as a maid for this family.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:48.48,0:11:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And they have a little boy.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:50.40,0:11:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A human boy, of course.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:52.98,0:11:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The family had adopted a dog before the boy was born.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:57.45,0:11:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The boy and the dog grew up like siblings.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:00.91,0:12:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But the dog died.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:09.42,0:12:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like me to erase a portion of your memory data?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:15.55,0:12:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't erase the memories of my husband.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:26.23,0:12:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This is horrible.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:28.64,0:12:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The victim is Bernard Lanke.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:31.40,0:12:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the leaders of a group defending the Robot Laws.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:33.98,0:12:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:35.73,0:12:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There must be tons of people who think badly of a scholar \Nwho insists on protecting the rights of robots like he did.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:41.70,0:12:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is how the body was found.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:48.12,0:12:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with the horns?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:50.83,0:12:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:52.92,0:12:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:02.64,0:13:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:04.43,0:13:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the site where Mont Blanc \Nof the Swiss Forestry Service was destroyed.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:08.31,0:13:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Horns.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:09.64,0:13:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying the same person \Nis responsible for both incidents?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:14.90,0:13:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Breaking a sturdy robot like Mont Blanc \Ninto pieces is impossible for humans.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:20.90,0:13:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, at the time of his murder,
Dialogue: 5,0:13:24.66,0:13:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,there was no trace of any other \Nhuman presence in Lanke's apartment.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:29.04,0:13:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"No trace of any other human presence"...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:31.25,0:13:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it, Gesicht.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:32.92,0:13:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Lanke was human!
Dialogue: 5,0:13:34.75,0:13:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:35.75,0:13:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Article 13 of the International Robot Laws says, \N"A robot may not harm or kill a human being."
Dialogue: 5,0:13:41.34,0:13:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's a robot out there that can kill a human,
Dialogue: 5,0:13:47.14,0:13:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it'd be the first time since the case eight years ago.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:56.02,0:13:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll find the perpetrator.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:58.07,0:14:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether they be a robot or \Na human, there is a devil inside them.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:10.66,0:14:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,A strange pedestal, isn't it?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:13.42,0:14:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Originally, the plan was to build \Na bronze statue of Mont Blanc on it.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:18.80,0:14:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Mont Blanc objected to it.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:23.22,0:14:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He said it would be wrong to ruin the scenic view \Nof the Alps with a bronze statue of himself.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:29.77,0:14:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only that, he insisted \Nhe would one day become scrap iron.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:34.44,0:14:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted to be chopped up, melted down, and recycled.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:40.36,0:14:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was still in his prime.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:44.70,0:14:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Mont Blanc was a true hero.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:50.04,0:14:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He joined the 39th Central Asian War as \Na member of the peace-keeping forces.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:56.13,0:15:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He not only helped the Kingdom of Persia \Nrestore peace from the chaos and turmoil,
Dialogue: 5,0:15:01.30,0:15:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but he also managed to apprehend \Nterrorists in hiding without bloodshed.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:05.47,0:15:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Without him, Asia could never have \Nreached the state of peace it has now.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:11.47,0:15:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He was also a poet.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:14.69,0:15:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He was able to sing with birds and \Nconverse with the trees of the forest.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:19.44,0:15:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Those people over there volunteered \Nto do this work with no compensation.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:25.20,0:15:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They all loved Mont Blanc, my son.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:31.37,0:15:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Mont Blanc was the guardian angel of the mountains.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:34.83,0:15:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In three days, tens of thousands...
Dialogue: 5,0:15:38.42,0:15:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,no, hundreds of thousands will come to \Nthe memorial to mourn the death of Mont Blanc.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:44.55,0:15:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Detective, this was no accident.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:49.64,0:15:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They say Mont Blanc was destroyed because of \Nthe huge tornado that happened just before the forest fire,
Dialogue: 5,0:15:57.90,0:15:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's not true at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:00.06,0:16:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Detective, please catch the person responsible for this.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:04.11,0:16:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do, then I swear I'll use these hands to...
Dialogue: 5,0:16:08.74,0:16:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the pride of Switzerland, \Nnay, the entire human race.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:12.83,0:16:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,May he remain forever in our hearts...
Dialogue: 5,0:16:34.39,0:16:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you awake, Gesicht?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:37.27,0:16:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Your maintenance check is finished.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:40.19,0:16:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Professor Hoffman.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:42.11,0:16:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how did it go?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:44.02,0:16:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, nothing out of the ordinary.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:46.86,0:16:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Except...
Dialogue: 5,0:16:48.07,0:16:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:49.70,0:16:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people think robots don't get tired,
Dialogue: 5,0:16:53.03,0:16:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but when you're this similar to humans, \Na robot can feel exhaustion.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:57.41,0:17:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,To put it another way, the human body \Nitself is nothing but a mechanism.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:02.08,0:17:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,With too much use, any mechanism can become fatigued.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:06.17,0:17:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Fatigued?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:08.80,0:17:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like you're dealing with rather difficult cases.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:12.51,0:17:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw Mont Blanc's memorial on TV, \Nbut I had to turn it off to keep from crying.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:19.52,0:17:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Some media have reported a theory that he self-destructed \Nfrom an electromagnetic anomaly in his body.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:25.36,0:17:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But as an expert on the subject,
Dialogue: 5,0:17:27.69,0:17:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe an advanced robot like him\N could experience such an elementary problem.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:35.58,0:17:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Think you'll track down whoever killed \Na robot that was loved by everyone?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:43.38,0:17:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it can't be that easy.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:46.84,0:17:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, the other case \Nyou're investigating looks complicated too.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:52.01,0:17:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The victim named Lanke...
Dialogue: 5,0:17:54.01,0:17:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw him several times on TV debates, \Nand it's not surprising he was targeted.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:59.85,0:18:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't necessarily doing anything wrong, \Nbut he had a sharp tongue.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:04.98,0:18:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like he was looking down on everyone.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:07.23,0:18:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That was bound to make some enemies.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:09.15,0:18:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The complete opposite of Mont Blanc.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:12.61,0:18:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A robot and a human.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:14.61,0:18:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,One with no enemies and the other with too many enemies.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:18.20,0:18:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder you're exhausted,\N juggling two cases at once like that.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:24.08,0:18:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask you a question?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:26.84,0:18:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:28.46,0:18:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it possible for a human to infiltrate \Na room without leaving any biological traces?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:34.63,0:18:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean traces so minuscule that \Nyour sensors cannot detect them?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:41.02,0:18:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:41.85,0:18:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an interesting question.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:44.60,0:18:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder...
Dialogue: 5,0:18:50.40,0:18:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my homework for next time.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:52.53,0:18:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry about all that.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:54.20,0:18:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This is supposed to be a place for you to relax.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:56.74,0:18:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No more shop talk.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:04.12,0:19:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been talking to my wife about taking time off for a trip.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:09.13,0:19:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, how nice.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:10.80,0:19:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to consider her schedule too, \Nso I don't know when it will happen.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:14.97,0:19:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Traveling is good.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:16.72,0:19:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Data shows that seeing the world yields \Npositive results for artificial intelligence.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:22.77,0:19:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How about doing something bold and going to Japan?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:25.69,0:19:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:26.94,0:19:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I went there once at the invitation \Nof one of my research buddies.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:32.61,0:19:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Tokyo is exotic and interesting.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:36.11,0:19:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan, huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:37.57,0:19:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll talk to my wife about it.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:39.87,0:19:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Gesicht, are you still having \Nthe dream you told me about before?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:47.96,0:19:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:48.75,0:19:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not trying to put you on the spot or anything,
Dialogue: 5,0:19:52.13,0:19:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm quite intrigued by dreams\N generated by artificial intelligence.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:56.34,0:20:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been academically proven that \Nartificial intelligence also carries a subconscious.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:02.72,0:20:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, it's rare to find a robot that actually has dreams.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:07.48,0:20:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When you feel up to it, could you tell me about it?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:10.86,0:20:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:11.94,0:20:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Twentieth-century psychiatrist Freud \Nonce said something to this effect.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:16.36,0:20:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dreams are expressions of reality,\N not just products of our imagination."
Dialogue: 5,0:20:40.97,0:20:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:47.23,0:20:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this a patrol-bot?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:50.15,0:20:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, seems like it.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:52.31,0:20:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The crime lab said they're done, \Nso I'm supposed to get rid of it.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:56.94,0:20:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Robby...
Dialogue: 5,0:21:00.66,0:21:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,May I take a look?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:04.33,0:21:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:05.83,0:21:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Feel free to take whatever parts you want.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:08.33,0:21:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They're junk, after all.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:13.96,0:21:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have the whole body for 500 ZEUS.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:19.09,0:21:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Something wrong?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:24.64,0:21:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:26.35,0:21:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:29.02,0:21:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:35.07,0:21:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your husband's memory chip.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:38.65,0:21:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I may be overstepping, but I thought you might want it.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:42.57,0:21:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, not at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:44.37,0:21:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sincerely grateful.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:46.54,0:21:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:47.91,0:21:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I should be going now.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:51.75,0:21:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:53.33,0:21:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you mind inserting it into me?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:58.21,0:22:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The memories could be painful.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:07.97,0:22:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They might cause you to malfunction.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:10.35,0:22:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If that happens, I'll take it out right away.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:15.02,0:22:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He's... right here.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:32.71,0:22:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ma'am, you have to stop!
Dialogue: 5,0:22:34.42,0:22:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Memories of his last moments are also stored there!
Dialogue: 5,0:22:37.88,0:22:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm taking it out!
Dialogue: 5,0:22:39.34,0:22:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What could this be?
Dialogue: 5,0:22:42.67,0:22:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what it is.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:45.64,0:22:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you see?
Dialogue: 5,0:22:47.10,0:22:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me project it.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:57.94,0:23:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This was when Robby stopped a car \Nat the checkpoint with his partner.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:07.95,0:23:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the suspect.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:18.08,0:23:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:20.21,0:23:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't have brought this to you.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:23.42,0:23:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how to apologize.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:25.47,0:23:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:27.64,0:23:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband reacted to \Nthe criminal's steel pipe immediately.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:31.97,0:23:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He had his stun gun at the ready.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:34.60,0:23:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:35.85,0:23:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It was odd that your husband, \Na patrol-bot, was attacked so easily.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:41.11,0:23:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is definitely an unusual case—
Dialogue: 5,0:23:43.19,0:23:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I mean.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:44.82,0:23:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a closer look.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:49.41,0:23:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see it because the memory chip is inside me.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:53.54,0:23:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,His partner was attacked.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:56.33,0:24:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Up until this moment, my husband had \Nregistered the criminal's movements.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:01.80,0:24:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the next moment,
Dialogue: 5,0:24:04.26,0:24:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,he was distracted by something.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:07.76,0:24:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the apartment where Lanke was murdered!
Dialogue: 5,0:24:15.18,0:24:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Pause it, please!
Dialogue: 5,0:24:17.98,0:24:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 5,0:24:19.65,0:24:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll zoom in.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:23.90,0:24:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a bird.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:25.61,0:24:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't the forensics team notice this?
Dialogue: 5,0:24:30.20,0:24:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You would've never spotted it unless \Nyou had this memory chip inserted.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:35.37,0:24:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband caught sight of this shadow in an instant, \Nand his identification system analyzed what it was.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:42.00,0:24:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it could jump from building to building like this...
Dialogue: 5,0:24:46.46,0:24:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:47.67,0:24:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But this...
Dialogue: 5,0:24:50.93,0:24:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't a robot.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:07.32,0:25:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A murder in a room with no trace of human activity.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:12.53,0:25:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The death of a robot loved by everyone.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:17.66,0:25:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Horns.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:37.31,0:25:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Identity confirmed.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:38.68,0:25:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please enter.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:11.05,0:26:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you a robot, Detective?
Dialogue: 5,0:26:13.84,0:26:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:14.51,0:26:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, I sure couldn't tell from your appearance.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:19.68,0:26:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get too close to him, your artificial intelligence \Ncould be compromised by his electromagnetic waves.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:25.52,0:26:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Use this protective gear.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:27.36,0:26:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be okay.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:28.73,0:26:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm impervious to electromagnetic waves.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:31.49,0:26:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 5,0:26:32.57,0:26:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm made of a special alloy, although I may not look like it.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:37.08,0:26:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That so?
Dialogue: 5,0:26:37.99,0:26:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you say so, but do be careful.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:42.71,0:26:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, four robots have fallen victim to him.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:09.32,0:27:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a laughably desperate barricade, isn't it?
Dialogue: 5,0:27:14.45,0:27:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the day, humans can't control \Ntheir fear without pitiful measures like this.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:26.75,0:27:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Brau-1589.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:36.93,0:27:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome, Robot Model HRS-0288, Inspector Gesicht.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:43.18,0:27:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So you are the most advanced detective robot?
Dialogue: 5,0:27:46.73,0:27:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems your identification system is still functioning.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:49.86,0:27:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It is indeed. Thank you.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:52.07,0:27:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's actually more sensitive than before.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:55.70,0:28:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Being deprived of the mode of locomotion, I can't help \Nbut be curious about what's happening out there.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:03.49,0:28:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I came here today because I wanted to ask you something.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:06.54,0:28:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 5,0:28:08.04,0:28:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What crossed the mind of a certain robot \Nwhen it killed a human eight years ago?
Dialogue: 5,0:28:17.09,0:28:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A legal scholar named Bernard Lanke was murdered,
Dialogue: 5,0:28:21.10,0:28:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but there were no traces of human presence at the scene.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:25.73,0:28:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Was the killer a human—
Dialogue: 5,0:28:28.31,0:28:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Or a robot?
Dialogue: 5,0:28:29.73,0:28:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it was a robot, why would it do such a thing?
Dialogue: 5,0:28:33.57,0:28:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The humans have already examined the deepest \Nrecesses of my murderous artificial intelligence.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:41.57,0:28:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They believed there must've been a defect,
Dialogue: 5,0:28:44.62,0:28:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but they couldn't find a thing.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:48.79,0:28:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,My artificial intelligence had no flaws at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:55.59,0:28:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine how terrified \Nthe humans were when they found that out?
Dialogue: 5,0:28:59.68,0:29:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they keep me locked up in a place like this.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:04.01,0:29:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're that afraid, they can just \Npull out this spear. Then I'd die.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:08.31,0:29:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But they can't even do that.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:16.53,0:29:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Gesicht.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:18.24,0:29:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to know more about\N someone who's committed a murder,
Dialogue: 5,0:29:21.53,0:29:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,why don't we exchange memory chips?
Dialogue: 5,0:29:24.91,0:29:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You might learn something new.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:39.26,0:29:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are some images I printed of Mont Blanc's \Ndestruction and Lanke's murder scene.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:44.72,0:29:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think these horns mean?
Dialogue: 5,0:29:48.73,0:29:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Among the ancient myths of Europe,
Dialogue: 5,0:29:51.60,0:29:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the god of death had horns.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:55.52,0:30:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Herne the Hunter, who takes the souls of warriors, \Nwas also called the "Horned King."
Dialogue: 5,0:30:01.70,0:30:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In Greek mythology, Hades is the king of the underworld.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:05.66,0:30:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Or perhaps, the lord of the \Nunderworld in Roman mythology,
Dialogue: 5,0:30:09.79,0:30:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Pluto.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:13.62,0:30:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Pluto.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:15.88,0:30:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever did these will strike again.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:20.26,0:30:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Mont Blanc, among the most advanced \Nof all robots, was destroyed so easily.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:26.64,0:30:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer should be clear to you by now.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:30.60,0:30:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The top-class robots created with \Nthe best technologies in the world.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:36.27,0:30:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Robots who can also be weapons of mass destruction.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:40.49,0:30:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You know the answer already, do you not?
Dialogue: 5,0:30:44.70,0:30:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Including you, there are six more.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:49.35,0:31:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm working.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:50.89,0:31:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't just stand there. It's distracting.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:54.89,0:31:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to have entered without your permission, sir.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:57.65,0:31:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The security seems to have been disabled.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:01.69,0:32:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not safe, considering your blindness.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:05.32,0:32:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No burglar would come all the way \Nto this wasteland to steal from me.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:09.82,0:32:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Sir Duncan—
Dialogue: 5,0:32:10.74,0:32:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:12.12,0:32:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you the new butler?
Dialogue: 5,0:32:14.12,0:32:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:15.20,0:32:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Bet they sent over yet another good-for-nothing.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:19.33,0:32:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name?
Dialogue: 5,0:32:20.67,0:32:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is North No. 2, sir.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:24.13,0:32:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What a dull and tasteless name.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:28.76,0:32:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The staffing agency told me \Nyou have a military background.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:34.81,0:32:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:35.85,0:32:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,During the 39th Central Asian War,
Dialogue: 5,0:32:39.19,0:32:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a butler for the commander-in-chief \Nof the British Army.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:42.32,0:32:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,A butler for a soldier, huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:32:45.36,0:32:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be a rather boorish sight.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:48.53,0:32:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I wear a cape in the presence of others.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:51.70,0:32:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:53.12,0:32:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So your whole body is a weapon.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:56.37,0:32:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Make me some tea, will you?
Dialogue: 5,0:32:58.04,0:32:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, sir.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:59.42,0:33:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,As for the type, I want...
Dialogue: 5,0:33:01.25,0:33:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Please rest assured.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:02.59,0:33:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All of your data is already downloaded.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:10.09,0:33:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My data, huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:33:13.85,0:33:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I came here, I had the chance to see a film.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:18.85,0:33:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Queen on the Satellite Orbit{\i0}.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:21.73,0:33:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I was deeply moved by how the music \Nand images came together as one.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:26.48,0:33:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that from your "data" as well?
Dialogue: 5,0:33:29.07,0:33:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I was profoundly moved from the bottom of my heart.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:32.11,0:33:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That film is over ten years old.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:35.49,0:33:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:38.00,0:33:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Every score I composed was a huge hit, \Nsweeping all the film music awards.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:42.38,0:33:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I was lauded as a blind musical genius.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:45.42,0:33:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Reviews from the media must \Nsurely be in that skull of yours too.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:50.80,0:33:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,"Even the genius Paul Duncan has run out of talent."
Dialogue: 5,0:33:54.76,0:33:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I right?
Dialogue: 5,0:33:56.47,0:33:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What a load of bollocks.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:57.72,0:34:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If I felt the urge, I could compose \Nas many scores as I want.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:01.77,0:34:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,My genius is alive and well.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:04.06,0:34:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I write the notes, and the people burst into applause.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:07.19,0:34:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They would leave the theater in tears.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:10.95,0:34:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that I can't compose. I won't.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:14.20,0:34:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Not for such stupid films.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:17.45,0:34:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But you were working just now.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:20.87,0:34:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a beautiful piece.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:24.38,0:34:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not for a film.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:26.75,0:34:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That piece is for me.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:29.01,0:34:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Only for me.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:35.64,0:34:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just like your name.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:37.89,0:34:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir?
Dialogue: 5,0:34:38.64,0:34:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Dull and tasteless.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:40.73,0:34:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A beautiful piece?
Dialogue: 5,0:34:42.77,0:34:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make me laugh.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:44.44,0:34:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A rubbish military weapon like you \Nhas no right to talk about my art!
Dialogue: 5,0:34:51.53,0:34:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,My apologies, sir.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:25.73,0:35:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How many did you kill?
Dialogue: 5,0:35:28.11,0:35:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir?
Dialogue: 5,0:35:29.07,0:35:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm asking how many people \Nyou killed in the Central Asian War.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:35.82,0:35:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The Robot Laws forbid me from harming humans.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:40.70,0:35:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. So you killed your own kind.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:45.04,0:35:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How many robots did you destroy?
Dialogue: 5,0:35:49.09,0:35:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Too many to count?
Dialogue: 5,0:35:53.34,0:35:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Go away.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:55.42,0:35:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A tasteless meal becomes even blander with you around.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:59.68,0:36:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I will take my leave, sir.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:27.29,0:36:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 5,0:36:28.87,0:36:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't touch my piano!
Dialogue: 5,0:36:32.42,0:36:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My apologies, sir.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:35.55,0:36:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You compose with your piano only, I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:38.84,0:36:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What about it?
Dialogue: 5,0:36:40.76,0:36:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You have so much cutting-edge \Nmusical equipment available to you.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:45.89,0:36:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That stuff is just like you.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:48.56,0:36:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A fake violin, a fake trumpet, a fake orchestra.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:54.78,0:36:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretend as they might, they're nothing but machines.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:59.57,0:37:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I don't put in artificial eyes.
Dialogue: 5,0:37:03.28,0:37:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything I could see with the help of machines is fake.
Dialogue: 5,0:37:08.08,0:37:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no need for it.
Dialogue: 5,0:37:10.62,0:37:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The real scenery is in my memories.
Dialogue: 5,0:37:15.75,0:37:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The real scenery...
Dialogue: 5,0:37:18.55,0:37:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The landscape of my hometown, \Ncaptured when I was able to see.
Dialogue: 5,0:37:22.55,0:37:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,When you were a child in Bohemia.
Dialogue: 5,0:37:26.06,0:37:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that from the data too?
Dialogue: 5,0:37:28.31,0:37:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing that truly matters in such nonsense.
Dialogue: 5,0:37:32.73,0:37:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The scenery of my hometown...
Dialogue: 5,0:37:35.44,0:37:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The green fields...
Dialogue: 5,0:37:38.53,0:37:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The gentle breeze...
Dialogue: 5,0:37:40.40,0:37:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 5,0:37:42.36,0:37:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that golden glow.
Dialogue: 5,0:37:48.45,0:37:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I will turn that scenery into music!
Dialogue: 5,0:39:07.62,0:39:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you not to touch my piano!
Dialogue: 5,0:39:12.00,0:39:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,My apologies, sir.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:14.62,0:39:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If a machine like you were to play from a score,\N any notes produced would be fake!
Dialogue: 5,0:39:21.17,0:39:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Duncan.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:22.59,0:39:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Please pardon my imposition, but I heard you \Nmoaning as you slept in your bedroom last night.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:29.56,0:39:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But it also sounded like you were humming.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:34.81,0:39:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I believe that melody would fit perfectly \Nwithin the piece you are composing now.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:42.69,0:39:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,At the section where you always stop midway.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:47.24,0:39:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not precise, but it went like this.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:53.12,0:39:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out!
Dialogue: 5,0:39:55.04,0:39:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no need for a robot like you.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:58.00,0:39:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave this residence!
Dialogue: 5,0:39:59.84,0:40:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 5,0:40:01.25,0:40:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an order. Leave!
Dialogue: 5,0:40:06.72,0:40:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd...
Dialogue: 5,0:40:11.39,0:40:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to learn how to play piano.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:15.27,0:40:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 5,0:40:16.64,0:40:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,As you say, no matter what I might play, \Nit may always be fake.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:23.23,0:40:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'd like to get as close as possible to the real thing.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:27.40,0:40:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A weapon like you could never play the piano!
Dialogue: 5,0:40:40.42,0:40:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 5,0:40:41.50,0:40:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's nothing for a tool of mass destruction to touch!
Dialogue: 5,0:40:44.34,0:40:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You belong on the battlefield!
Dialogue: 5,0:40:48.63,0:40:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:52.30,0:40:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why I'd like to learn to play piano.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:56.23,0:40:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I don't ever want to go to a battlefield again.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:03.86,0:41:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 5,0:41:06.36,0:41:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 5,0:41:09.61,0:41:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 5,0:41:12.07,0:41:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 5,0:41:19.50,0:41:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Mom!
Dialogue: 5,0:41:25.21,0:41:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, don't go!
Dialogue: 5,0:41:27.26,0:41:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 5,0:41:30.05,0:41:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 5,0:41:33.35,0:41:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mom!
Dialogue: 5,0:41:40.31,0:41:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you there, North No. 2?
Dialogue: 5,0:41:45.69,0:41:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you not to come into my bedroom.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:49.65,0:41:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Duncan, your breakfast is ready.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:57.29,0:41:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I fired you.
Dialogue: 5,0:42:02.04,0:42:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you still there?
Dialogue: 5,0:42:13.22,0:42:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times do I have to tell you?
Dialogue: 5,0:42:18.43,0:42:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't touch my piano!
Dialogue: 5,0:42:21.48,0:42:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Duncan, please listen.
Dialogue: 5,0:42:23.98,0:42:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I've gotten a little better.
Dialogue: 5,0:42:26.73,0:42:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,"Gotten a little better"?
Dialogue: 5,0:42:28.69,0:42:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The only improvement a machine can \Nmake is to play with more precision!
Dialogue: 5,0:42:34.11,0:42:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I will try to play the melody you hum in your sleep, sir.
Dialogue: 5,0:42:54.51,0:42:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The sounds you produce are not music!
Dialogue: 5,0:43:01.02,0:43:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,These bloody things!
Dialogue: 5,0:43:03.56,0:43:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,"Just input the data, and you can create infinite melodies"?!
Dialogue: 5,0:43:11.15,0:43:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not music at all!
Dialogue: 5,0:43:16.11,0:43:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You're breaking the instruments.
Dialogue: 5,0:43:19.99,0:43:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to protect your fellow machines?
Dialogue: 5,0:43:23.16,0:43:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, then. How many of your own kind did you destroy?
Dialogue: 5,0:43:29.75,0:43:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Take off your cape and show the world \Nthe hideous weapon that is your body!
Dialogue: 5,0:43:35.01,0:43:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,With that body of yours, \Nhow many of your kind did you kill?
Dialogue: 5,0:43:41.31,0:43:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Even a weapon of mass destruction is programmed \Nto behave obediently in front of its master, huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:43:49.82,0:43:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 5,0:43:51.32,0:43:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you some genuine and accurate data about me.
Dialogue: 5,0:43:56.66,0:44:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I moan in my sleep...
Dialogue: 5,0:44:00.62,0:44:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been tormented by a nightmare for so many years.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:04.20,0:44:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not a nightmare. It really happened.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:10.92,0:44:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,My real name isn't Paul Duncan.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:14.72,0:44:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Paulo Holy.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:16.09,0:44:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born into a poor family in Bohemia.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:19.89,0:44:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,My father died before I was old enough to remember.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:23.77,0:44:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I was struck by a serious illness from birth,
Dialogue: 5,0:44:26.64,0:44:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and my eyesight was poor,\N so my only joy was singing songs.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:33.78,0:44:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother was a beautiful woman.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:36.07,0:44:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in rags, she would turn the heads \Nof men when she walked down the street.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:41.95,0:44:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why that parvenu approached her.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:46.62,0:44:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And my mother became blinded by her greed for his money.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:54.00,0:44:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,She must've felt burdened by me.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:58.05,0:45:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sickly and stood in her way.
Dialogue: 5,0:45:02.39,0:45:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So she abandoned me!
Dialogue: 5,0:45:06.52,0:45:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sent to a boarding school in England.
Dialogue: 5,0:45:11.52,0:45:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no friends, and my weak \Nbody left me bullied year-round.
Dialogue: 5,0:45:17.95,0:45:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was desperate to continue my study of music.
Dialogue: 5,0:45:24.37,0:45:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I must've strained myself continuously because, \Nat one point, I developed a persistent fever,
Dialogue: 5,0:45:29.50,0:45:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and even my music studies could not continue.
Dialogue: 5,0:45:40.80,0:45:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sent around from hospital \Nto hospital, but my condition worsened.
Dialogue: 5,0:45:47.98,0:45:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctors gave up on me, \Nand I never heard from my mother.
Dialogue: 5,0:45:54.56,0:45:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I was going to die.
Dialogue: 5,0:45:59.03,0:46:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What a fitting last moment for an abandoned child.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:05.95,0:46:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when a Japanese doctor appeared.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:09.37,0:46:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Technically, he wasn't a doctor because he was unlicensed.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:15.29,0:46:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I will save your life.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:18.42,0:46:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But you might go blind as a result.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:26.18,0:46:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The surgery was a success.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:29.31,0:46:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But just as the unlicensed doctor said, \Nmy eyesight deteriorated day by day.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:36.90,0:46:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,With the little time I had left,
Dialogue: 5,0:46:39.11,0:46:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I threw myself even more into the study of music.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:44.61,0:46:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Music was all I had.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:48.08,0:46:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,More music!
Dialogue: 5,0:46:50.62,0:46:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,More!
Dialogue: 5,0:46:52.04,0:46:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,More!
Dialogue: 5,0:46:53.50,0:46:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,More!
Dialogue: 5,0:46:58.25,0:47:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, the darkness came.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:04.63,0:47:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A few years later, I was informed of my mother's death.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:08.18,0:47:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She never was able to marry that parvenu.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:12.81,0:47:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard she died all alone.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:15.85,0:47:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Serves her right for abandoning her child.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:19.23,0:47:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know what? This castle belonged to that parvenu.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:24.53,0:47:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,From Paulo Holy to the genius Paul Duncan.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:28.83,0:47:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I became a maestro of the music world \Nand made the castle mine.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:34.08,0:47:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother!
Dialogue: 5,0:47:35.62,0:47:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what you wanted.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:39.17,0:47:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what you sought at \Nthe cost of abandoning your child!
Dialogue: 5,0:47:44.55,0:47:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Mother, I will show you what is truly important.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:50.31,0:47:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The landscape of our hometown that you deserted!
Dialogue: 5,0:47:53.27,0:47:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I will turn that magnificent scenery into music!
Dialogue: 5,0:47:57.73,0:48:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll show you that there are some \Nthings people should never abandon!
Dialogue: 5,0:48:07.49,0:48:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Duncan.
Dialogue: 5,0:48:09.49,0:48:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother—
Dialogue: 5,0:48:10.83,0:48:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Silence!
Dialogue: 5,0:48:14.87,0:48:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll write you a letter of recommendation. \NLeave this place tomorrow.
Dialogue: 5,0:48:49.95,0:48:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'd like to learn how to play piano.
Dialogue: 5,0:48:53.79,0:48:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Because I don't ever want to go to a battlefield again.
Dialogue: 5,0:49:58.39,0:50:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess he improved a little.
Dialogue: 5,0:50:25.63,0:50:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Blasted machine must be recharging himself \Nin preparation for tomorrow's departure.
Dialogue: 5,0:50:45.44,0:50:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he having a nightmare?
Dialogue: 5,0:50:53.99,0:50:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Robots have dreams too?
Dialogue: 5,0:51:26.31,0:51:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,"It's not that I can't compose. I won't," huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:51:33.61,0:51:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 5,0:51:36.28,0:51:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,North No. 2.
Dialogue: 5,0:51:39.12,0:51:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,North No. 2! Hey!
Dialogue: 5,0:51:44.71,0:51:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He really left, huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:51:52.84,0:51:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I really can't compose anymore.
Dialogue: 5,0:52:12.32,0:52:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How long are you going to make me wait?
Dialogue: 5,0:52:14.69,0:52:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When is the replacement butler coming—
Dialogue: 5,0:52:17.16,0:52:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, my name is Marshall from MCM Pictures.
Dialogue: 5,0:52:20.45,0:52:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're just a movie guy.
Dialogue: 5,0:52:22.79,0:52:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong, Sir Duncan?
Dialogue: 5,0:52:25.79,0:52:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I just fired a butler robot the other day.
Dialogue: 5,0:52:30.50,0:52:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do you want?
Dialogue: 5,0:52:32.46,0:52:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm actually calling about a film score.
Dialogue: 5,0:52:37.59,0:52:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A job offer, huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:52:39.51,0:52:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me the details. I might be interested.
Dialogue: 5,0:52:43.35,0:52:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 5,0:52:45.06,0:52:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wondering if you would consent \Nto the reuse of one of your old scores.
Dialogue: 5,0:52:49.81,0:52:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What? You're not asking for a new piece?
Dialogue: 5,0:52:52.40,0:52:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, not at all!
Dialogue: 5,0:52:53.98,0:52:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my understanding that you had retired, sir.
Dialogue: 5,0:53:00.49,0:53:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Use it however you want.
Dialogue: 5,0:53:02.62,0:53:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Sir Duncan—
Dialogue: 5,0:53:06.96,0:53:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There is a new message.
Dialogue: 5,0:53:13.09,0:53:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Russell from the Planning Office \Nat the British Philharmonic Orchestra.
Dialogue: 5,0:53:18.05,0:53:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is in regards to the performance \Nof your suite we discussed before.
Dialogue: 5,0:53:22.64,0:53:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, we have decided \Nto cancel it due to various circumstances.
Dialogue: 5,0:53:26.39,0:53:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We are very sorry about this.
Dialogue: 5,0:53:28.06,0:53:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If another opportunity arises, we will...
Dialogue: 5,0:53:51.54,0:53:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I heard you moaning,
Dialogue: 5,0:53:54.04,0:53:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and I believe that melody would fit perfectly.
Dialogue: 5,0:55:46.49,0:55:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Duncan.
Dialogue: 5,0:55:49.37,0:55:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I have returned.
Dialogue: 5,0:55:53.12,0:55:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What now?
Dialogue: 5,0:55:54.29,0:55:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I told you to leave.
Dialogue: 5,0:55:56.92,0:55:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to Bohemia.
Dialogue: 5,0:55:59.21,0:56:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,To your birthplace.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:02.13,0:56:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What business did you have there?
Dialogue: 5,0:56:04.76,0:56:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to collect songs.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:08.47,0:56:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In the process of collecting many \Nfolk songs from that region,
Dialogue: 5,0:56:12.85,0:56:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I found it.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:14.35,0:56:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The melody you hum in your sleep.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:20.61,0:56:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I will sing it now.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:22.28,0:56:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 5,0:56:23.65,0:56:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to hear a machine sing!
Dialogue: 5,0:56:26.24,0:56:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't intrude on my nightmare any further!
Dialogue: 5,0:56:29.53,0:56:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Humans have things we would rather forget!
Dialogue: 5,0:56:34.75,0:56:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But, sir, your dream is not a nightmare.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:40.25,0:56:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not something that should be erased like my dreams.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:46.01,0:56:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as you said, I'm nothing but a weapon.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:50.35,0:56:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 39th Central Asian War,\N I neutralized many enemy robots...
Dialogue: 5,0:56:56.77,0:57:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I destroyed tens of thousands of my own kind.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:03.19,0:57:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Those memories—the memories \Nof killing countless of my kind—
Dialogue: 5,0:57:08.53,0:57:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,are played back again and again in my artificial brain.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:13.58,0:57:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I met an old man in Bohemia.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:18.08,0:57:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He was very knowledgeable about folk songs,
Dialogue: 5,0:57:20.83,0:57:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and he knew that particular song as well.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:24.13,0:57:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He also remembered that there was \Na wonderful singer of that song.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:32.18,0:57:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:36.39,0:57:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The data I have in my mind about \Nyou includes that of your mother.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:43.40,0:57:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother did not abandon you \Nwhen you were suffering from illness.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:49.99,0:57:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,She approached a multimillionaire, \NJonathan Thorn, to attain treatment.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:57.79,0:58:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how she afforded the astronomical fee \Nfor the doctor who saved your life.
Dialogue: 5,0:58:06.63,0:58:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You were never abandoned.
Dialogue: 5,0:58:09.47,0:58:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother was right by your side when you went blind.
Dialogue: 5,0:58:16.43,0:58:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But sensing your hatred toward her, \Nshe couldn't extend her hand.
Dialogue: 5,0:58:24.56,0:58:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 5,0:58:27.82,0:58:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That can't be.
Dialogue: 5,0:58:29.99,0:58:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 5,0:58:31.61,0:58:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,When you remember your hometown, \Nare you not excluding a very important memory?
Dialogue: 5,0:58:39.58,0:58:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The old man in the village told me how you and \Nyour mother held hands and sang this song together
Dialogue: 5,0:58:46.63,0:58:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as you watched the sun setting\N into the fields of your homeland.
Dialogue: 5,0:59:32.92,0:59:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 5,0:59:40.68,0:59:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 5,0:59:45.94,0:59:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 5,0:59:48.15,0:59:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only the song of a machine.
Dialogue: 5,0:59:52.32,0:59:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Your dream isn't a nightmare.
Dialogue: 5,0:59:56.70,0:59:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Not like mine.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:03.00,1:00:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,North No. 2...
Dialogue: 5,1:00:06.75,1:00:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,don't ever go back to the battlefield.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:16.63,1:00:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's practice the piano.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:22.18,1:00:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 5,1:02:25.22,1:02:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,North No. 2!
Dialogue: 5,1:02:26.97,1:02:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, North No. 2!
Dialogue: 5,1:02:29.77,1:02:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir?
Dialogue: 5,1:02:32.23,1:02:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's finally finished. Give it a listen.
Dialogue: 5,1:02:35.61,1:02:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I would love to listen to it, sir.
Dialogue: 5,1:02:39.44,1:02:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,However, right now...
Dialogue: 5,1:02:40.70,1:02:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's the matter?
Dialogue: 5,1:02:43.16,1:02:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Something is approaching this direction.
Dialogue: 5,1:02:46.37,1:02:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,"Something"?
Dialogue: 5,1:02:48.08,1:02:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a friend visiting you, perhaps?
Dialogue: 5,1:02:52.04,1:02:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear the news from Switzerland a few days ago, sir?
Dialogue: 5,1:02:56.96,1:02:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The news from Switzerland?
Dialogue: 5,1:02:58.88,1:03:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, about the robot called Mont Blanc \Ngetting destroyed in a tornado?
Dialogue: 5,1:03:06.47,1:03:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A tornado occurred about 100 km \Nfrom here just a moment ago.
Dialogue: 5,1:03:17.90,1:03:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Some sort of threat is approaching.
Dialogue: 5,1:03:23.53,1:03:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 5,1:03:26.28,1:03:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I shall return soon.
Dialogue: 5,1:03:28.74,1:03:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,North No. 2!
Dialogue: 5,1:04:02.32,1:04:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,North No. 2.
Dialogue: 5,1:04:05.99,1:04:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,North No. 2!
Dialogue: 5,1:04:11.79,1:04:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,North...
Dialogue: 5,1:04:20.42,1:04:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world...
Dialogue: 5,1:04:29.47,1:04:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What is happening?
Dialogue: 5,1:04:39.31,1:04:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,North No. 2...
Dialogue: 5,1:04:52.37,1:04:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 5,1:05:01.34,1:05:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that song.
Dialogue: 5,1:05:04.13,1:05:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The song is spreading across the entire sky.
Dialogue: 5,1:05:15.47,1:05:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,North No. 2 is...
Dialogue: 5,1:05:22.65,1:05:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,North No. 2 is singing.
Dialogue: 5,1:05:36.83,1:05:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop singing out there and come home soon.
Dialogue: 5,1:05:42.92,1:05:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,North No. 2,
Dialogue: 5,1:05:46.42,1:05:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it's time for our piano practice.
Dialogue: 5,1:06:14.74,1:06:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really awesome!
Dialogue: 5,1:06:16.04,1:06:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 5,1:06:36.39,1:06:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a snail?
Dialogue: 5,1:06:38.47,1:06:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,1:06:44.40,1:06:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 5,1:06:47.61,1:06:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be Atom.
Dialogue: 5,1:06:52.61,1:06:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
